
* Book: Law of Cooperatives. By Charles T. Autry and Roland F. Hall. American Bar Association, 2009.


=Description=

"A practical and insightful introduction to the law of cooperatives and how this form of business is differentiated from other business entities! Attorneys who have had limited exposure to the cooperative form often face a steep learning curve when negotiating with cooperatives on behalf of their clients or when attempting to represent a new client that happens to be organized as a cooperative. Although cooperatives are similar in many respects to other businesses, certain characteristics are distinctly different and not necessarily intuitive to an attorney familiar with corporations and partnerships."


